| Online Reputation Is Hard To Do                                    |
|   from the to-say-nothing-of-trust dept.                           |
|   posted by kdawson on Sunday June 03, @17:15 (The Internet)       |
|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/03/1947227              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Symblized writes "A new article from InformationWeek argues that not only
does the Web need ways to verify identity, it also needs [0]better ways
to measure reputation . The article uses Digg, Wikipedia, and eBay as
examples and muses whether their models could be applied more widely.
There's also a [1]profile of Opinity, a company that tried to introduce a
reputation system and didn't make it. Choice quote from a source in the
article: 'The idea of a transferable, semantic reputation is identity
nirvana.'"

Discuss this story at:
    http://slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/03/1947227

